	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories The motive for the fatal shooting of a taxi boss on the R102 in Tongaat, north of Durban, on Monday night has still not been established, KwaZulu-Natal police said on Tuesday. The 52-year-old taxi boss sustained gunshot wounds to his chest and mouth when unknown gunmen shot him at about 20:25, police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele told News24. "He was certified dead at the scene. The motive for the attack is unknown. A case of murder was opened at Tongaat police station for investigation," she said. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  